subsection.p:
A proportion is a statement that two ratios are equal.  For example,
    \dfrac{7}{5} = \dfrac{x}{6}     
To solve this proportion, we multiply both sides by the LCD, 30, to get
    \alert{30}\left(\dfrac{7}{5}\right) \amp = \left(\dfrac{x}{6}\right)\alert{30}
        42 \amp = 5x \amp \amp \blert{\text{Divide both sides by 5.}}
        x = \dfrac{42}{5} = 8.4

